  <div class="node">
        <h2 class="title"><a href="/events-randall-monroe-xkcd-tonight-sf-singularity-summit-oct-3-4-nyc">Events:  Randall Monroe (xkcd) tonight in SF, Singularity Summit Oct 3-4 in NYC</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Mon, 2009-09-21 14:40.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_5"><a href="/archives/cat_announcements.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_5">Announcements</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_95"><a href="/topic/robocars" rel="tag" title="The future of computer-driven cars and deliverbots" class="taxonomy_term_95">Robocars</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>Two events I will be at&#8230;</p>

<p>Tonight, at 111 Minna Gallery in San Francisco, we at EFF will be hosting a <a href="http://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2009/09/effs-geek-reading-xkcd">reading by Randall Monroe</a>, creator of the popular nerd comic &#8220;xkcd.&#8221;   There is a regular ticket ($30) and a VIP reception ticket ($100) and just a few are still available.   Payments are contributions to the EFF.</p>

<p>In two weeks, on Oct 3-4, I will be speaking on the future of robot cars at the <a href="http://www.singularitysummit.com/">Singularity Summit</a> in New York City.  Lots of other good speakers on the podium too.</p>

<p>See you there&#8230;</p>
</div>
